                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#109r" facs="110">fols. 109r, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#117v #118r" facs="119">117v, 118r</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> The Burial of the Blessed Virgin <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#41v" facs="043">Fol. 41v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7805Peter">Peter</persName> 's Denial of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#144v" facs="146">Fol. 144v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> rescues the three young men in the fiery furnace</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#1r #7r #13v #29v #42r #50r" facs="002 008 015 031 043 051">folss. 1r, 7r, 13v, 29v, 42r, 50r, </locus> (haräg);
                  <locus target="#67v #72v #84r #95v" facs="069 074 085 097">67v, 72v, 84r, 95v, </locus> (multiple full stops and a line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#98r #121r" facs="099 122">98r, 121r</locus> (multiple full stops)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001"> f. ir(ecto), middle</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Excerpt of <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2934RepCh215">Malkǝʾ-hymn to
                                                  Raphael</title>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001"> f. ir(ecto), top and bottom</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    notes of late ownership, Taddäsä Gobäna, and “This Dawit belongs to all of us.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#55r" facs="056">Fol. 55r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    A small, round symbol in the margin marks the midpoint of the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</ref>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#145r" facs="146"> f. 145r, col. 1, lower</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note of secondary ownership: Däbtära Tägäñ Wändǝm, in blue ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#145r" facs="146"> f. 145r, top right</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (in pen): Name: Bǝrhane Alämǝn[yo]
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#145v" facs="147">Fol. 145v</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note, upside down. <q>This Psalter belongs to Abba Mäl’äku, but is given to the congregation (Mahǝbär)</q>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#36 #60 #84 #128" facs="037 061 085 129">Fols. 36, 60, 84, 128</locus>
                    <desc>
                    blue yarn is sewn into the top margin to mark content as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 3–5 and 8–10
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#2v #10v #15r #15v #16v" facs="004 012 016 017 018">Fols. 2v, 10v, 15r, 15v, 16v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#12r #13v #31v #39v #43v" facs="013 015 033 041 045">Fols. 12r, 13v, 31v, 39v, 43v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., lines of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#4v #8v #9v #10r #13v" facs="006 010 011 015">Fols. 4v, 8v, 9v, 10r, 13v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., erasure markings are visible;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#19r #19v #21v #32v #76r" facs="020 021 023 034 077">Fols. 19r, 19v, 21v, 32v, 76r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#14v" facs="016">Fol. 14v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line throughout the codex (throughout) But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, four Coptic chain stitches attached by bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards covered with tooled leather, headband and tailband.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                      <material key="leather"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
